	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />int8_t is a signed 8-bit integer. sizeof gives the size of an object, in bytes. sizeof (char) is defined to be 1. numeric_limits&lt;type&gt;::digits gives the number of bits in a type. But, why C++ for learning 6502?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


